Class LynxUsbDeviceConfiguration

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.qualcomm.robotcore.hardware.configuration.DeviceConfiguration
      • com.qualcomm.robotcore.hardware.configuration.ControllerConfiguration<LynxModuleConfiguration>
        • com.qualcomm.robotcore.hardware.configuration.LynxUsbDeviceConfiguration
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<DeviceConfiguration>

    public class LynxUsbDeviceConfiguration
extends ControllerConfiguration<LynxModuleConfiguration>
    A Lynx USB Device contains one or more Lynx modules linked together over an RS485 bus. The one of these which is connected externally to USB is termed the 'parent'; the others are called 'children'.
